item.title: The A1100 Seattle Silicon at SuperComputing 15
item.description: Anyone loosely following AMD’s efforts with ARM intellectual property would have had on their periphery the noise of the A1100 product aimed at servers, codenamed Seattle. The idea was to use AMD’s back-end expertise to produce a multi-core ARM chip based on eight A57 cores for server and professional embedded systems, supporting up to 128GB of RDIMM memory and two 10GBase-KR Ethernet ports. The secret sauce of the processor is in the co-processors – a cryptographic one to offload dedicated acceleration of encryption/decryption or compression/decompression, and a system control co-processor that focuses on security and acts like a ‘processor within a processor’ with its own Ethernet connection, RAM, ROM and IO connectivity for remote management and sensing.

item.title: What Is Paint Made Of?

item.title: YouTuber CJ So Cool Shares Hospital Photo After Allegedly Being Shot 4 Times During Home Invasion
item.description: YouTube star Cordero James Brady, referred to fans as CJ So Cool, says he was shot multiple times during a home intrusion on Thursday. As per Brady’s Instagram Story, the supposed assault happened in the early long stretches of Thursday at 3 a.m. also, left him hospitalized. “Up until this point, I’m doing alright,” he added close by a message requesting that fans keep him and his youngsters in their requests.
